        "details": {
            "description": "<p>Ghostly attackers knock the tables about, send dishes flying, and pull fleeing creatures into the room.</p>",
            "disable": "<p><span data-pf2-check=\"religion\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"34\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Religion</span> (expert) to say an Iroran prayer and put the haunt temporarily to rest, <span data-pf2-check=\"occultism\" data-pf2-traits=\"haunt\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"38\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">Occultism</span> (master) to create a ward against future hauntings.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 12
            },
            "reset": "<p>The haunt deactivates after 1 minute. It re-forms at the same times every day, 7 a.m. and 7 p.m., which is when the monks had their morning and evening meals. If at least two people cook a meal in the kitchen, share a meal in the refectory, and utter a prayer to Irori before the meal, the haunt becomes permanently disabled and doesn&rsquo;t re-form.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(1 action) The haunt sends a flurry of objects hurtling across the room. All creatures in the room are battered by the ghostly objects, taking [[/r 3d10+14 #force]]{3d10+14 Force damage} (<span data-pf2-saving-throw=\"reflex\" data-pf2-traits=\"damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"\" data-pf2-dc=\"36\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save).</p>"
